===== Involved rules descriptions:

[iamf][Rule #3] id: assert-codec-config-obu
Section 3.5
Codec Config OBU checks:
- There SHALL be exactly one Codec Config OBU with a given identifier in a set of Descriptors.
- codec_id indicates a 'four-character code' (4CC) to identify the codec. Supported values: Opus, mp4a, fLaC, ipcm.
- num_samples_per_frame SHALL NOT be set to zero.
- audio_roll_distance SHALL always be a negative value or zero.
- audio_roll_distance SHALL be set to -R when codec_id is set to Opus, where R = ceil(3840 / num_samples_per_frame).
- audio_roll_distance SHALL be set to -1 when codec_id is set to mp4a.
- audio_roll_distance SHALL be set to 0 when codec_id is set to fLaC or ipcm.

[iamf][Rule #17] id: assert-common-profile-restrictions
Section 4
Common restrictions on the IA Sequence for all profiles:
- The maximum size of an OBU SHALL be limited to 2MB.
- There SHALL be only one unique Codec Config OBU.
- num_sub_mixes SHOULD be set to 1.
- num_audio_elements SHOULD be set to at most 28.
- When num_layers = 1, both output_gain_is_present_flag and recon_gain_is_present_flag SHALL be set to 0.

